		<content:encoded><![CDATA[There is someone who works at the Associated Press, probably more than one!, that makes a decision about which news stories are important enough to be an alert for mobile users. And they decided that Oprah's imminent announcement to end her show in 2 years is worthy:

<a title="AP thinks this is critical news by troyh, on Flickr" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/troyh/4118700382/"><img class="centered" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2475/4118700382_96135a13e5_o.jpg" alt="AP thinks this is critical news" width="320" height="480" /></a>

I can't decide if this is dumber than their alert about <a href="http://troyandgay.com/blog/2009/10/09/ap-mobile-notifications/">golf in the 2016 Olympics</a>. Does this even merit an alert if you work for Oprah and will lose your job in 2011?

They accept (and seem to ignore) feedback at <a href="mailto:mnnfeedback@ap.org">mnnfeedback@ap.org</a>.]]></content:encoded>
